Obviously not. The monster merely roared and tried to charge directly at Sasalin. Fortunately, although Sasalin was large in size, he was still quite agile and managed to dodge in time. However, Nisi couldn't help but scream, nearly slipping off Sasalin's smooth scales.
"How can we kill them?" Nisi shouted.
"Take aim at their heads!"
"This is too difficult!"
Sasalin let out a screech, circled around, and flew toward the mountain he called home. The black monster followed closely behind, but when it was attacked from behind by flames, it became somewhat flustered. The monster had yet to realize it now had an additional opponent. Sasalin slowed down, then struck the monster's head fiercely with his tail, knocking it off course, which made the creature even more panicked.
The monster roared, emitting a hissing sound from its throat as it flew straight upward, continuously spitting something into the air. Suddenly, the surrounding area turned pitch black, as if the creature were absorbing the light from the sky and replacing it with an eternal night.
Sasalin's vision went black as he tried to step back, only to find himself colliding with a tree branch and tumbling down to the ground below. The monster seemed to know exactly where Sasalin had fallen and flew straight toward him, taking the mass of clouds with it.
"Kayer!" Tenuk shouted as he burst out of the storm clouds, circling around, trying to spot Nishi and Sasarin in the darkness below. "What should we do, Kayer...? Kayer, where are you?"
Nisi struggled to her feet. She felt certain she had broken bones, but her strange, unnatural healing ability had already begun to take effect. The situation was different for Sasalin—he lay lifelessly on the ground, propped up against a tree he had crushed. Nisi tried to walk toward Sasalin, but her vision was dark and nearly nonexistent. Terrifying shadows surrounded her, and something was screaming in the darkness.
A terrible club-like tail smashed violently onto the ground, knocking Nixi off her feet. She noticed the tail was swinging wildly, but it seemed its target was not her. Nixi struggled to see that the monster was roaring and furiously scratching at its own shadow. Something was teleporting in the darkness, waiting for the right moment to strike the monster.
Suddenly, a gunshot broke the air, and the monster immediately fell silent, collapsing lifeless on the ground. The surrounding darkness dissipated, revealing the truth of the situation. Kyle stood on top of the monster's corpse, holding a rifle in his hands, breathing heavily.
"That was... one of the weirdest shadow jumps I've ever done... Tanto Kartholon..." Kayer panted. For some reason, his eyes glowed with a dark light, and a dark energy surged within him. But as Kayer was about to speak, his organic armor regained its color, and his eyes returned to their normal yellow.
After a while, Nishi finally realized what had happened. They all knew that Kayel possessed a strange shadow ability, but he rarely used it because most people considered this power to be extremely evil and terrifying. However, Nishi didn't know that Kayel could use this ability in any darkness. Moreover, from Kayel's reaction, it seemed that he himself was also quite surprised.
"Are you okay?" Nixi couldn't help but ask.
"I'm fine. I killed that thing, and I'll be back to normal soon." Kael looked at his "masterpiece" when Ternuk landed beside him, transforming back into his original Spast form.
Now, the monster was no longer moving, allowing them to take a good look at what it really was. Its skin was jet black and glossy, covered with a layer of slimy liquid that clung tightly to its body. It had four wings and four legs, each ending in long, slender claws, and two straight horns grew from its skull.
Tennok and Kayel hadn't even had time to figure out what the hell it was when a monster screeched and leaped out from the nearby bushes. At that very moment, a familiar car crashed into the side of the monster, sending it sliding a short distance before coming to a stop at Nishi's feet. Without hesitation, Nishi grabbed the shotgun and fired directly at the monster's head, killing it instantly.
"Ugh..." Retwick muttered as he sat in the driver's seat, then clumsily turned off the engine and climbed down from the truck. "Uh, I didn't mean to. Are you all okay?"
"You missed all the fun!" Tnuke muttered. "Where did you run off to?"
"it was you who left me behind. I've done my best to catch up..." Retwick sighed. "Excuse me, what are these horrible things?"
Rietvik's question was answered by Sasarin, who had already risen to his feet. He was covered in wounds and scratches, looking a bit dazed, but his injuries didn't seem to be serious.
"You killed the Corrupted! Those infected monsters. When the Corruption attacked your gods, these creatures were left behind here."
"Did you mean... that we... helped kill the terrifying god-like monster?" Tenuk stammered slightly.
"Yes, that's true. There might be even more corrupt ones. But I can't shoot them in the head. I don't have a gun. And it's not fair to fight two against one, right?" Sashalin walked up to Kayer and patted his head. "Thank you, little guy. You remind me of my old friend Arcading. Just you aren't as ruthless as him, nor do you have his power to destroy the universe."
"Uh... thank you... I think..." Kayel shrugged. "So, uh, have we completed the mission?"
Nisi shrugged her shoulders, picked up her camera, and took a few photos of the monsters, which she was sure were already dead. Then, she pulled out her favorite dagger—the exquisite Reaper's dagger—and began cutting off one of the monster's horns, then the other. However, the moment Nisi finished cutting, the monsters suddenly ignited and quickly turned to ash. The horns she had cut off also turned to ash.
“Well... this is definitely a mixed blessing..." Nishi sighed. "At least I still have the photos, right?"
